# OpenClaw Documentation Lookup

When a conversation involves **OpenClaw** — installation, configuration, CLI commands,
gateway setup, channels, tools, agents, MCP integration, or troubleshooting — always
consult the `openclaw-docs` MCP server before relying on training data.

OpenClaw is a newer project and your training data may be outdated or incorrect.

## Available tools (from `openclaw-docs` MCP server)

| Tool | When to use |
|---|---|
| `openclaw_docs_search` | Find specific topics (e.g. "gateway auth token", "telegram channel") |
| `openclaw_docs_section` | Read a full documentation section by heading |
| `openclaw_docs_index` | List all available doc pages to discover what exists |
| `openclaw_docs_chunk` | Read raw docs from a character offset (for continuation) |

## Workflow

1. **First**, run `openclaw_docs_search` with relevant keywords
2. If you need more detail, use `openclaw_docs_section` with the heading from search results
3. If unsure what docs exist, start with `openclaw_docs_index`

## When to consult automatically

- User asks about OpenClaw installation or setup
- User mentions `openclaw.json`, gateway, or OpenClaw CLI
- You are generating OpenClaw configuration and want to verify correctness
- You encounter an OpenClaw error or unexpected behavior
- User references channels (Telegram, Discord, Slack, etc.) in an OpenClaw context
